<BaseLayout title="keepitmovin vs. context layers" description="Compare coding-session continuity with broad AI memory and context products.">
  <article class="docs-content prose standalone-prose container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Comparison</p><h1>keepitmovin vs. general context layers</h1>
    <p>General context products connect many sources and make personal or company knowledge available across assistants. keepitmovin does not ingest Slack, email, documents, or SaaS accounts.</p>
    <h2>The keepitmovin niche</h2>
    <p>It watches a local coding session, keeps one project-owned handoff current, and moves that task to another terminal tool when needed.</p>
    <h2>Choose by scope</h2>
    <p>Choose a context layer for broad, reusable memory. Choose keepitmovin for local coding-task continuity with no hosted knowledge store. They can coexist.</p>
    <p><a href="/privacy">Read the local-data boundary →</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
